response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: Divisor Sum\", \"description\": \"Find the sum of all proper divisors of a given number.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef divisor_sum(n: int) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `n` (int): A positive integer.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the sum of all proper divisors of the input number, excluding 1 and the number itself.\\n\", \"code\": \"\\nimport math\\n\\ndef divisor_sum(n: int) -> int:\\n    # Initialize the sum to 0\\n    total = 0\\n    \\n    # Iterate over all numbers from 2 to n-1\\n    for i in range(2, math.floor(math.sqrt(n)) + 1):\\n        if n % i == 0:\\n            # If `i` is a divisor, add it and its corresponding divisor (n // i) to the sum\\n            total += i + n // i\\n    \\n    return total\\n\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert divisor_sum(28) == 28\", \"assert divisor_sum(12) == 16\", \"assert divisor_sum(24) == 28\", \"assert divisor_sum(36) == 84\"] }"
